<TITLE> BNP ward chief gunned down in Old city</font> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 9 (bdnews24.com)BNP ward commissioner Haji Ahmed Hossain was gunned down in Bangshal, Old Dhaka, on Tuesday, police said. Bangshal police chief Abdul Mannan told bdnews24.com that Hossain, also president of Dhaka City's Jubo Dal south chapter, was shot at around 8.30pm and rushed to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. A duty doctor there told bdnews24.com that the local BNP leader was dead on arrival, but Hossain's family transferred him to Square Hospital where he was put on life support for a short time. He was taken off life support at around 10pm, Jubo Dal leader Qayyum Chowdhury told bdnews24.com.
